1 dams within the State to draw down water levels in anticipation of a flood
2 event that is likely to cause substantial damage or injury to persons or property.
3 Waivers may only be issued if the Governor, in consultation with the Secretary
4 of Natural Resources or designee, has significant reason to believe doing so
5 will decrease the risk of substantial damage to persons or property within the
6 State. Dam operators operating under a waiver shall be required make every
7 effort to minimize the environmental impact of a water level drawdown under
8 the authorized waiver.
